<html metal:use-macro="main_template">
  <head metal:fill-slot="head" tal:omit-tag>
    <script>
      function hypothesisConfig() { return {firstRun: true} }
    </script>
    <script type="text/javascript" defer="defer">
      <metal:main use-macro="load: embed.txt" />
    </script>
    <title>Hypothesis</title>
  </head>
  <body metal:fill-slot="body" tal:omit-tag>
    <div class="help-page">
      <header class="help-page-content masthead-small">
        <metal:main use-macro="load: header.pt" />
      </header>
      <article class="help-page-content">
        <section class="help-page-section" tal:condition="is_help">
          <h2 id="installation" class="help-page-heading">Installation</h2>
          <p class="help-page-lede">There are a couple of installations of Hypothesis to choose from:</p>
          <div class="numbered-list grid">
            <div class="column-1-2"><div class="numbered-list-item">If you want to annotate and comment on documents then install our browser extension.</div></div>
            <div class="column-1-2"><div class="numbered-list-item">If you wish to install Hypothesis on your own site then head over to GitHub.</div></div>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="help-page-section" tal:condition="is_onboarding">
          <h2 id="getting-started" class="help-page-heading">Getting started</h2>
          <p class="help-page-lede">Now you have the extension up and running. It's time to
            start annotating some documents.</p>
          <div class="numbered-list grid">
            <div class="column-1-2"><div class="numbered-list-item">Create an account using the sidebar on the right of the screen.</div></div>
            <div class="column-1-2"><div class="numbered-list-item">Go forth and annotate! The sidebar can be enabled by clicking the icon in the url.</div></div>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="help-page-section" tal:condition="is_index">
          <h2 id="getting-started" class="help-page-heading">Getting started</h2>
          <p class="help-page-lede">Great, you've got the server up and running, you're now ready to start kicking the tires.</p>
          <div class="numbered-list grid">
            <div class="column-1-2"><div class="numbered-list-item">Create an account using the sidebar on the right of the screen.</div></div>
            <div class="column-1-2"><div class="numbered-list-item">Create some annotations on this page or use this dev bookmarklet: <metal:main use-macro="load: h:templates/bookmarklet.pt" /></div></div>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="help-page-section">
          <h2 id="key-features" class="help-page-heading">Key Features</h2>
          <p class="help-page-lede">We're constantly looking to improve Hypothesis to fit in with your workflows. Check out our Roadmap to see what's coming up. In the mean
            time we've highlighted a few of our favorites:</p>
          <div class="grid feature-content">
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-3">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-earth"></i> Annotate Anywhere</h3>
              <div class="feature-content">
                <p>Annotate any web page or PDF document using the Chrome extension
                  on any website.</p><!--We provide a bookmarklet for browsers other than Chrome
                if you would like to see a Hypothesis extension for another browser
                please let us know.-->
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-3">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-copy"></i> Instantly Shareable</h3>
              <div class="feature-content">
                <p>Every annotation has itâ€™s own url which you can bookmark or share.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-3">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-locked"></i> Privacy</h3>
              <div class="feature-content">
                <p>Annotations are either public and viewable by everyone
                  with access to the document or private and visible only to you.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="help-page-section">
          <h2 id="key-features" class="help-page-heading">Annotation Types</h2>
          <p class="help-page-lede">There are a few different types of annotations that can be created
            with the application:</p>
          <div class="grid feature-content">
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-2">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-copy"></i> Notes</h3>
              <div class="feature-content styled-text">
                <p>Create a  <em>note</em> by selecting some text and clicking the button
                  that appears above the selection. You can then add your own
                  comments and tags.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-2">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-highlighter"></i> Highlights</h3>
              <div class="feature-content">
                <p>Quick  <em>highlights</em> can be created with the highlighter mode;
                    enable this by using the  highlighter <i class="help-icon h-icon-highlighter"></i> button in the application
                    menu.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-2">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-comment"></i> Comments</h3>
              <div class="feature-content">
                <p>Leave a  <em>comment</em> on the document by using the comment <i class="help-icon h-icon-plus"></i> button
                  in the application menu.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
            <section class="feature column-tablet-1-2">
              <h3 class="feature-heading"><i class="feature-icon h-icon-reply"></i> Replies</h3>
              <div class="feature-content">
                <p>You can  <em>reply</em> to any annotation by using the  reply <i class="help-icon h-icon-reply"></i> action
                  found at the bottom of each card.</p>
              </div>
            </section>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="help-page-section">
          <h2 class="help-page-heading">Resources</h2>
          <div class="styled-text">
            <ul>
              <li>View the <a href="">roadmap</a> to see what's coming up.</li>
              <li>Request features, report bugs and meet other users in our <a href="/">discussion forums</a>.</li>
              <li>If you need help please don't hesitate to <a href="mailto:support@hypothes.is">get in touch</a>.</li>
              <li>Visit <a href="/">our website</a> to learn more about the project.</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </section>
        <section class="help-page-section" tal:condition="is_index">
          <h2 id="contributing" class="help-page-heading">Contributing</h2>
          <div class="styled-text">
            <p>Hypothes.is is an open source effort licensed under a 2-Clause <a
                href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_licenses">BSD License</a>,
              sometimes referred to as the "Simplified BSD License" or the "FreeBSD
              License". Development is coordinated through <a
                href="https://github.com/hypothesis">our Github repository</a> utilizing
              the issue tracking and wiki tools provided there. Additionally, we manage a
              mailing list which you can subscribe to by sending an email to <a
                href="&#x6d;&#x61;&#x69;&#x6c;&#116;&#111;&#58;&#100;&#101;&#x76;&#x2b;&#x73;&#x75;&#x62;&#115;&#99;&#114;&#105;&#98;&#x65;&#x40;&#x6c;&#x69;&#x73;&#116;&#46;&#104;&#121;&#112;&#x6f;&#x74;&#x68;&#x65;&#x73;&#46;&#105;&#115;">&#100;&#101;&#x76;&#x2b;&#x73;&#x75;&#x62;&#115;&#99;&#114;&#105;&#98;&#x65;&#x40;&#x6c;&#x69;&#x73;&#116;&#46;&#104;&#121;&#112;&#x6f;&#x74;&#x68;&#x65;&#x73;&#46;&#105;&#115;</a>
              (<a href="http://list.hypothes.is/archive/dev">archive</a>).</p>
            <p>Note the <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/wiki">project
                wiki</a>, including a <a
                href="http://docs.hypothes.is/roadmap/">roadmap</a>, detailed <a
                href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/wiki/_pages">descriptions</a> and <a
                href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/wiki/Mockup-index">mockups</a> of
              upcoming features, and <a href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/issues">current
                issues</a> needing development attention. Additionally, our <a
                href="https://groups.google.com/forum/#!forum/hypothesis-forum"
                target="_blank">forum</a> is a great place to get answers and offer feedback.
              After you're done familiarizing yourself with the project landscape we
              recommend reading our <a
                href="https://github.com/hypothesis/h/blob/develop/CONTRIBUTING.rst">contributor
                guide</a> which details our work-flow, conventions and licensing administrivia.
              Additionally, please feel free to join us in <a
                href="http://webchat.freenode.net/?channels=hypothes.is">#hypothes.is</a> on <a
                href="http://freenode.net/">freenode</a> and subscribe to our mailing list.</p>
          </div>
        </section>
      </article>
      <div class="help-page-sidebar">
        <div id="help-1">
          <p>Show and hide the sidebar using the <i class="h-icon-comment"></i> button</p>
        </div>
        <div id="help-2"></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
